  "label": "Obsidian Scar Cavern",
  "description": "Obsidian Scar Cavern is a basalt-walled hollow cut into Sablecrown Peak along a glassed seam left by empyrean discharge. Its floor is sheeted in vitrified slag and fractured obsidian, with fused fortification rubble embedded in the rock like aggregate in black cement. The air carries a persistent metallic tang, and bruise-hued auroral light filters inward as a cold sheen across wet stone. Narrow chimneys and collapsed shelves segment the chamber into blind pockets and echoing runs.",
